author: By Julian Robinson
description: The decision to drop the investigation into WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange was announced by Sweden's Director of Public Prosecution, Marianne Ny.
title: Sweden drops its prosecution against WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange

author: Matthew Hughes
description: Sweden's Director of Public Prosecutions has announced it has dropped the investigation into Julian Assange's rape charges, which have dogged the Australian-born Wikileaks founder since ...
title: Sweden just dropped the Julian Assange rape investigation

author: Dominic Chopping
description: Swedish prosecutors said they have decided to discontinue a probe into alleged rape targeting WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange, but his lawyers say he is likely to remain holed up in Ecuador’s London embassy.
title: Sweden Ends Probe Into WikiLeaks Founder Julian Assange

description: Sweden's top prosecutor has said she has dropped a rape investigation into Julian Assange, the founder of WikiLeaks.
title: Julian Assange says he does not 'forgive or forget' as Swedish rape investigation is dropped

author: Reuters
description: Swedish prosecutors said on Friday they had dropped an investigation of WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange over a rape allegation.
title: Sweden Drops Julian Assange Investigation But UK Police Say He Still Faces Arrest

description: Mit WikiLeaks und Transparenzdenken inspirierte Julian Assange libertäre Parteien und Menschen weltweit. Zehn Jahre später ist davon nicht mehr viel übrig.
title: Julian Assange: Himmel und Hölle der Nerd-Bewegung

author: http://xml.zeit.de/autoren/F/Catharina_Felke/index, http://xml.zeit.de/autoren/K/Eike_Kuehl/index.xml
description: Auch wenn Schweden die Ermittlungen gegen den WikiLeaks-Gründer einstellt, wird er sich nicht frei bewegen können. Sechs Fragen und Antworten zum Fall von Julian Assange
title: Julian Assange: Ein freier Mann ist er noch nicht

description: Julian Assange, founder of WikiLeaks, has won his battle against extradition to Sweden, which wanted to question him about a rape allegation. He has spent nearly five years inside the Embassy of Ecuador in London to avoid being sent to Sweden, which announced Friday that the investigation has been discontinued.
title: Chronicle of Julian Assange's battle against extradition

author: Lizzie Dearden
description: Julian Assange will be arrested if he leaves the Ecuadorian embassy despite Sweden dropping its sexual assault investigation, British police have confirmed. A spokesperson for the Metropolitan Police said that despite Sweden's European arrest warrant for the WikiLeaks founder being lifted, he was under a separate warrant for skipping bail.
title: Julian Assange will still be arrested if he leaves Ecuadorian embassy

author: Oliver JJ Lane
description: Swedish Police officially dropped their seven-year long investigation into rape accusations against Wikileaks founder Julian Assange.
title: Sweden Drops Investigation of Wikileaks' Assange, But UK Police Will Still Arrest If He Leaves Embassy
